title: Women’s soccer: First-place Stanford defeats WSU in double overtime - Thu, 22 Oct 2015 PST
text:
Averie Collins scored in the 108th minute Thursday as Pac-12 Conference-leading Stanford defeated host Washington State 2-1 in double overtime in women’s soccer. 
Haley Rosen assisted on the goal for the Cardinal (13-2-0, 7-0-0). 
Maddy Haro scored in the first half for the Cougars (11-4-0, 4-3-0).
